<item>
            <title>[STORM-3679] misuse of nodeId as hostname in LoadAwareShuffleGrouping</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/STORM-3679</link>
                <project id="12314820" key="STORM">Apache Storm</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;LoadAwareShuffleGrouping misuses nodeId as the hostname and it causes consistent invalid DNS queries for &quot;hostnames&quot; like 2a1f2cf3-c701-4621-9e93-640b4e63be48-&amp;lt;ip&amp;gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes excessive unnecessary loads on nscd and DNS. Also because of this bug, every target tasks will be treated as at least RACK_LOCAL because if an ip address can&apos;t be determined, YahooDNSToSwitchMapping treats it as DEFAULT_RACK. This doesn&apos;t impact WORKER_LOCAL and HOST_LOCAL though.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
